        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 7:13PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 713 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Hamlin, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hamlin, Tornado, Alum Creek, Teays Valley, West Hamlin, Palermo,
Griffithsville, Sweetland, Sod, Yawkey, Branchland, and Myra.

This includes Route 119 near mile marker 61, and between mile markers
63 and 67.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
